## Build Specification

### Reference Implementation: PathFinder

Before writing any code, read PathFinder's structure:

```
/home/mario/projects/pathfinder/
├── app/              ← Next.js app directory
├── components/       ← React components
├── lib/              ← Utilities
├── data/             ← JSON file storage (real data lives here)
├── package.json      ← Node.js config to reference for versions
├── tsconfig.json     ← TypeScript config to copy
└── WAI-Spoke/        ← Wheelwright context (v1 format)
```

Use PathFinder's `package.json` for package versions. Use PathFinder's `tsconfig.json` as the base.

### Data Model

```typescript
// src/types/index.ts

export interface Track {
  id: string           // nanoid or uuid
  name: string
  description: string
  category: string     // e.g. "Learning", "Career", "Project", "Habit"
  tags: string[]
  created_at: string   // ISO-8601
  updated_at: string
  items: TrackItem[]
}

export interface TrackItem {
  id: string
  track_id: string
  title: string
  description: string
  status: "not_started" | "in_progress" | "complete"
  order: number
  blocked_by: string[]    // array of TrackItem ids — dependency graph
  time_estimate?: number  // minutes, optional
  time_spent?: number     // minutes, optional
  notes?: string
  completed_at?: string   // ISO-8601
}

export interface Progress {
  total: number
  complete: number
  in_progress: number
  not_started: number
  blocked: number         // items whose blocked_by has incomplete items
  pct: number             // 0-100, rounded
  velocity?: number       // items completed per day over last 7 days
}
```

### Base Variant (Build This First)

**What it is:** Next.js 14 + TypeScript + Tailwind + JSON file storage. Single user, no auth, no database. Get it working fast.

**Application structure:**
```
tracks/
├── WAI-Spoke/                      # DO NOT MODIFY (except WAI-State.json, WAI-Lugs.jsonl)
├── data/
│   └── tracks.json                 # created on first write, initialized as []
├── src/
│   ├── app/
│   │   ├── layout.tsx              # root layout, Tailwind base, nav bar
│   │   ├── page.tsx                # dashboard — all tracks with progress bars
│   │   ├── globals.css             # Tailwind directives
│   │   ├── tracks/
│   │   │   ├── new/
│   │   │   │   └── page.tsx        # create track form
│   │   │   └── [id]/
│   │   │       ├── page.tsx        # track detail: items + progress + add item
│   │   │       └── items/
│   │   │           └── [itemId]/
│   │   │               └── page.tsx  # edit item (status, notes, time)
│   │   └── api/
│   │       └── tracks/
│   │           ├── route.ts        # GET /api/tracks, POST /api/tracks
│   │           └── [id]/
│   │               ├── route.ts    # GET, PATCH, DELETE /api/tracks/[id]
│   │               └── items/
│   │                   ├── route.ts          # POST /api/tracks/[id]/items
│   │                   └── [itemId]/
│   │                       └── route.ts      # PATCH, DELETE /api/tracks/[id]/items/[itemId]
│   ├── lib/
│   │   ├── storage.ts              # readTracks(), writeTracks(), computeProgress()
│   │   └── utils.ts                # nanoid wrapper, date helpers
│   └── types/
│       └── index.ts                # Track, TrackItem, Progress interfaces
├── README.md                       # SEE README SPECIFICATION BELOW — write this file
├── package.json
├── tsconfig.json
├── next.config.js
├── tailwind.config.ts
└── postcss.config.js
```

**Storage layer (`src/lib/storage.ts`):**
```typescript
// Read data/tracks.json — return Track[] or [] if file missing
export function readTracks(): Track[]

// Write Track[] to data/tracks.json (create data/ if missing)
export function writeTracks(tracks: Track[]): void

// Compute Progress from TrackItem[] — pure function, no I/O
export function computeProgress(items: TrackItem[]): Progress
```

**Key UI behaviors:**
- Dashboard: grid of track cards — name, category, tag chips, progress bar (% + N/M label)
- Track detail: items in order, status badges clickable (cycles not_started → in_progress → complete), blocked items shown with lock icon and "blocked by [title]" label
- Add item form inline on track detail page (no separate route needed)
- Empty state on dashboard: "No tracks yet — create your first one"
- All mutations via API routes (no server actions for v0.1.0)

**Package versions** — check PathFinder's package.json for actuals, but use at minimum:
- `next`: 14.x
- `react` + `react-dom`: 18.x
- `typescript`: 5.x
- `tailwindcss`: 3.x
- `vitest`: latest

### Best Variant (Document, Don't Build Yet)

The best variant is v0.2.0+ scope. Document it in README.md so users understand the roadmap. Do NOT implement it now.

**Best variant adds:**
- PostgreSQL + Prisma ORM (replace JSON storage)
- NextAuth.js (GitHub + Google OAuth)
- tRPC for type-safe API
- Multi-user: shared tracks, comments, team progress
- Playwright E2E tests + GitHub Actions CI/CD
- Full analytics: velocity charts, streak tracking, comparative analytics
- PathFinder integration: sync job applications as track items
- Minder integration: sync tasks as track items

**Best variant stack:**
```
Frontend: Next.js 14 + React 18 + TypeScript + Tailwind CSS
Backend:  Next.js API Routes + tRPC
Database: PostgreSQL + Prisma ORM
Auth:     NextAuth.js (GitHub, Google)
Testing:  Vitest + Playwright
CI/CD:    GitHub Actions
Deploy:   Vercel (recommended)
```

